title.narrative: 1.3 POSITIVE PARENTING

description.narrative: National program on positive parenting is developed and modelled, which contributes to Early Childhood Development. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020, More young girls and boys (0 to 6), especially the most vulnerable are nurtured, stimulated and have access to quality early learning

title.narrative: National program on positive parenting is developed and modelled

description.narrative: The COVID-19 pandemic constrained;the positive parenting programme, limiting to a great extent the ability to engage stakeholders at decentralised level in the actual implementation of interventions planned. The launch was reprogrammed 3 times in the year and finally realised with UNICEF support on the 31th anniversary of the Convention on the;Rights of the Child;on November 20th, under the high patronage of the head of government – who gave a special authorization to organize this event despite the gathering restrictions- , and with the participation of 6 Ministers involved in its implementation in four selected sites nationwide and of key partners. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:29/12/2020
